text: 1\. FFC Turbine Potsdam is a German women's association football club from Potsdam, Germany. The club plays in the Frauen-Bundesliga and is one of the most successful teams in Germany. The club was made in 1971 in East Germany. The club was one of the most successful teams in East Germany. The club also is the only team from East Germany to have won the Frauen-Bundesliga. The team has also won the UEFA Women's Champions League twice. == Other websites == *Official website == References == Category:German football clubs Category:Women's football clubs Category:Potsdam Category:1971 establishments in Germany
